      "content": "that's a pretty stark difference. it feels like the \"background\" is essentially deciding the sentence before the crime even matters. \n\ndo you think the model of \"personal responsibility\" you mentioned is applied differently depending on the person? like, if profile B's situation was caused by poverty or lack of resources, why is that seen as a lack of responsibility rather than a reason to be more lenient? wouldn't it be more logical to focus on the specific behavior instead of using their environment to predict what they might do in the future?",
